Suggested change to avoid the manual iteration and to simplify the `TxToJSON` call. I think it's slightly easier to follow, but I don't have a strong opinion either way.
```suggestion
    CTxUndo* undo {nullptr};
    auto it = std::find_if(block.vtx.begin(), block.vtx.end(), [tx](CTransactionRef t){ return *t == *tx; });
    if (it != block.vtx.end()) {
        // -1 as blockundo does not have coinbase tx
        undo = &blockUndo.vtxundo.at(it - block.vtx.begin() - 1);
    }
    TxToJSON(*tx, hash_block, result, chainman.ActiveChainstate(), undo, TxVerbosity::SHOW_DETAILS_AND_PREVOUT);
    return result;
```

